From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000011 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Date: Tue, 22 Jul 2025 22:45:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] riscv: configs: add vsrves01_defconfig

Add a minimal defconfig for the VLSI VSRVES01 SoC (CAT Board
reference design) that enables:

  - ARCH_VLSI + ARCH_RV32I + NONPORTABLE (rv32 only, no C, no FPU,
    no IRQ_STACKS, no vendor extensions);
  - RISCV_SBI_V01 for the in-house SBI firmware;
  - uartlite earlycon @ 0x12000000 (console=ttyUL0);
  - the VLSI MAC ethernet driver + Micrel KSZ9131 PHY;
  - SLUB_TINY + JUMP_LABEL + BPF JIT, with block layer disabled;
  - INITRAMFS_SOURCE="catboard.cpio" (rd_* decompressors disabled
    so the cpio must be a raw archive next to the kernel build).

Typical use:

  make ARCH=riscv CROSS_COMPILE=riscv32-unknown-linux-musl- \
       vsrves01_defconfig
  cp /path/to/catboard.cpio .
  make ARCH=riscv CROSS_COMPILE=riscv32-unknown-linux-musl- \
       Image.vri

NOTE: the original esmil branch shipped a 3.5 MiB binary
catboard.cpio at the kernel-tree root.  We deliberately omit the
binary from this patch - it does not belong in a kernel-tree patch
and is staged into the build directory by the board
override-kernel.sh hook instead.

This patch is a board-support shim and unlikely to land upstream
as-is in this exact form.

Origin: esmil/linux vsrv branch f84f11fb4d6f (defconfig only, no
        binary cpio)

Signed-off-by: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Sungjoon Moon <sumoon@seoulsaram.org>
